ssumed boundaries between affixation, compounding and syntactic constructions play a very minor role. It shows that Early Sranan word-formation is characterised by the absence of superstrate derivational affixes, the use of free morphemes as derivational markers and of compounding as the major word-formation strategy. The emergence of Early Sranan word-formation involved multiple sources (the input languages, universals, language-internal development) and different mechanisms (reanalysis of free morphemes as derivational markers, adaptation of superstrate complex words, transfer from the substrates and the creation of innovations). The findings render untenable theoretical accounts of creole genesis based on one explanatory factor, such as superstrate or substrate influence.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCreole dialects, EnglishzSuriname. 0aSranan languagexWord formation. 4aKreolistik. 4aMorphologie. 4aSprachkontakt. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aCreole Studies.  aLanguage Contact.  aMorphology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2009z978311021954808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LIN